addAsset(address,uint256,address).details: The asset must not already be in the portfolio.      When an asset is added, a rebalance must be called to re-calculate the proportions of the assets.      And buy the asset from DEXs.

params._priceFeed: The address of the price feed contract for the asset.
params._proportion: The proportion of the portfolio to allocate to the new asset.
params._token: The address of the token to add.

changeAssetProportion(address,uint256).details: The asset must already be in the portfolio. Only the fund owner can call this function.      The proportion of the base currency can only be modified by changing the allocations of the other currencies.

params._proportion: The new proportion of the portfolio to allocate to the asset, expressed in PERCENTAGE_FACTOR.
params._token: The address of the token to modify.

params._priceFeed: The address of the price feed contract for the base currency (WETH)
params._swapRouter: The address of the Uniswap V3 router
params._weth: The address of the WETH contract

deposit(uint256).details: This function is payable and will receive ETH from the user. The function will wrap the ether sent by the user into WETH.

params._nftId: The ID of the token to deposit funds for.

getAssetProportion(address).details: The share returned is the target share, not the actual share.      The actual share share is calculated by dividing the token USD value by the funds total value.

params._token: The address of the ERC20 token to get the share of.

returns._0: The theoretical share of the portfolio for the token.

getAssetValue(address).details: The value is calculated by multiplying the ERC20.balanceOf(this) by the priceFeed.

params._token: The address of the token to get the fund value of.

returns._0: USD value of the fund for a specific asset.

getNFTShare(uint256).details: The share is calculated by dividing the NFT value by the total value of the portfolio.

params._nftId: The ID of the NFT to get the share of.

returns._0: The share of the portfolio for the NFT with 4 decimals of precision.

getNFTValue(uint256).details: The value is calculated by multiplying the NFT share by the total value of the portfolio.

params._nftId: The ID of the NFT to get the value of.

returns._0: The value of the portfolio for the NFT with 8 decimals of precision.

getPortfolioValue().details: The value is calculated by summing the value of each asset in the portfolio.      To get the value of each asset, we need the ERC20 balance of the fund contract and the priceFeed.

returns._0: Portfolio value in USD with 8 decimals of precision.
An array of all the tokens in the portfolio.

params.user: the address of the user to invite

returns._0: the token ID of the newly minted token

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

rebalance().details: The rebalance is done by swapping the assets that are above or below the target proportion.      The rebalance is done in 2 steps:      1. Sell the assets that are above the target proportion.      2. Buy the assets that are below the target proportion.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

withdraw(uint256,uint256).details: the WETH balance of the contract will be unwrapped to ETH and sent to the user.

params._amount: The percentage of your share to withdraw, expressed in PERCENTAGE_FACTOr. - e.g. for 50%, amount = 0.5*PERCENTAGE_FACTOR(50.00%)
params._nftId: The ID of the token to withdraw funds from.

addAsset(address,uint256,address).notice: Adds a new asset to the portfolio. When adding an asset, the owner specifies the share of the fund         the asset must represent, but the actual balance is 0. The balance is updated when the asset         is bought through rebalancing.

changeAssetProportion(address,uint256).notice: modifies the proportion of an asset in the portfolio.

deposit(uint256).notice: Deposit function called by users that will deposit funds for a portfolio share.         This rebalances the amount of shares each owner has.

getAssetProportion(address).notice: Returns the portfolio share of a specific token.

getAssetValue(address).notice: Returns the USD value of the fund for a specific asset.

getNFTShare(uint256).notice: Returns the share of the portfolio for a specific NFT.

getNFTValue(uint256).notice: Returns the value of the portfolio for a specific NFT.

getPortfolioValue().notice: Returns the total value of the portfolio in USD.

getRemainingProportion().notice: Returns the unallocated proportion of the portfolio that sits in WETH.

getTokens().notice: Returns all the tokens in the portfolio.

invite(address).notice: invites a user to join the fund

rebalance().notice: Rebalances the portfolio by swapping assets to reach the target proportions.

withdraw(uint256,uint256).notice: Withdraw funds from a portfolio share. This rebalances the amount of shares each owner has.
